# MPE CSS conventions

## Selectors

Target `.markdown-body`, `.markdown-preview`, and `body`. Packages are fully inlined (no `@import` in output).

## Naming

| Layer | Pattern | Example |
| ----- | ------- | ------- |
| Source | `vscode-preview-<slug>[-light\|-vN-desc].css` | `vscode-preview-beacon-light.css` |
| Package | `themes/mpe/<tier>/<slug>/style.less` | `experimental/beacon-light/style.less` |
| Family folder | kebab-case | `graphite-code`, `cpp-modern` |

Dark = no suffix; light = `-light`. Exceptions: Studio (light-only `studio`), Phosphor amber as warm sibling. Register `tier: "released" | "experimental"` in the build registry (new work → experimental).

## New family or variant

1. Add CSS under `themes/addons/vscode-preview/original/<family>/`
2. Register in `variants` in `build-mpe-global.mjs` with `slug`, `tier: "experimental"`, `label`
3. Run `node themes/addons/vscode-preview/build-mpe-global.mjs`
4. Update `themes/README.md`, `themes/mpe/README.md`, and the family `README.md`
5. **Commit** that unit (see `repo-theme-map` — commit after major changes)

## Shared tokens

- Do not duplicate all of `_syntax-tokens.css` inside a family file
- Stronger C++ refine only when needed (see `original/graphite-code/_cpp-syntax-refine.css` + `appendSyntaxRefine`)
- Diagram CSS tokens only for v3-style overlays (`appendDiagramTokens`)

## After every source CSS change

Rebuild MPE packages. Prefer editing `original/`, not generated `themes/mpe/**/style.less`. When the change is a finished family/variant (not mid-tweak), commit.
